name: Crispy Smashed Potatoes with Walnut Dressing

steps.instruction:
Made by Molly Baz and can be found [here](https://www.bonappetit.com/recipe/crispy-smashed-potatoes-with-walnut-dressing)

### Prep
- Coarsely chop the walnuts

### Steps
1. Place a rack in center of oven; preheat to 450°
2. Place potatoes in a large pot and cover with water.
3. Add 1 cup salt and bring to a boil. Immediately reduce heat to medium-low, bring to a simmer, and cook until potatoes are just cooked through and pierced easily with a fork, about 15 minutes (time will vary depending on the size of your potatoes; be careful not to overcook as they’ll fall apart when smashed)
4. Drain and transfer potatoes to a rimmed baking sheet. Let cool slightly.
5. Place another rimmed baking sheet on top, then push down firmly to smash potatoes (alternately, use the bottom of a mug or measuring cup to smash each one individually)
6. Drizzle ⅓ cup oil over potatoes, then toss to coat; season lightly with salt and black pepper. Roast potatoes until crispy and golden brown, 35–40 minutes.
7. Meanwhile, cook walnuts, anchovies, and remaining ⅓ cup oil in a small saucepan over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, until anchovies are disintegrated and walnuts are golden brown, 6–8 minutes
8. Transfer to a small bowl, finely grate garlic over, and toss to combine. Mix in raisins and Aleppo-style pepper; season with salt.
9. Spread sour cream on a large plate. Top with potatoes and spoon walnut sauce over. Scatter herbs over and serve with lemon wedges alongside.

ingredients.note: Such as parsley, dill, cilantro, and or basil
